707834f-a.text:
Second Ave., east side, south from East 37th to and including 35th Streets. Note the hand ball courts in St. Gabriel's Park, that are under
construction by the W.P.A.
April 6, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

707829f-a.text:
Second Avenue, at East 35th Street, as
photographed from atop the St. Gabriel's branch of the New York Public Library at No. 30 East 36th
Street.
To the left are the handball courts in the
western portion of St. Gabriels Park. The Second Avenue "E1" darkens the roadbed. It's 34th Street station barely appears at the margin. In the background, at Madison Sqquare are the distinctive buildings of the Metropolitan and the New York Life lInsurance Co's.
September, 1939
Gift of Beecher Ogden

707831f-a.text:
Second Avenue, west side, north from E. 35th Street.
January 7, 1939
Somach Photo Service
New York City

707832f-a.text:
Second Avenue, east side, north from E. 35th Street, showing in the foreground the westerly portion of St. Gabriel's Park. Across same and appearing on the north side of 35th Street are the Library, Sall and Parochial School of the same name. The church spire is in the center, atop the church which faces on the south side of 37th Street. In the distant background are ornate
structures forming Tudor City.
January 7, 1939
Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

707833f-b.text:
Second Avenue, east side, from East 35th to 37th Sttreets, showing St. Gabriels Park (35th-36th Streets), and the Midtown ueens Tunnel Plaza (36th-37th Streets). Both of these open areas extend to First Aenue. The buildings shown are on the eastside of same and the north side of E. 37th Street. Both of these photos are taken from a passing 2nd Avenue "E1" train.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
